### SEO Best Practices
- Use semantic HTML (`<header>`, `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<article>`, `<section>`)
- Include proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3)
- Add alt text to all images
- Use Next.js `<Image>` component for optimization
- Implement structured data (JSON-LD) where appropriate
- Create dynamic sitemap.xml and robots.txt
- Ensure mobile responsiveness
- Optimize Core Web Vitals (LCP, FID, CLS)

## Code Style & Standards

### TypeScript
- Use strict mode
- Define interfaces for all props and data structures
- Avoid `any` type - use `unknown` if truly needed
- Use type inference where obvious
- Export types alongside components

### File Naming
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `DashboardLayout.tsx`)
- Utilities: camelCase (e.g., `formatCurrency.ts`)
- Pages: lowercase with hyphens (Next.js convention)
- CSS Modules: `ComponentName.module.css`

### Component Structure
```typescript
'use client' // Only if needed (client interactivity)

import { ComponentProps } from './types'

interface Props extends ComponentProps {
  // Define props
}

export default function ComponentName({ prop1, prop2 }: Props) {
  // 1. Hooks
  // 2. Derived state
  // 3. Event handlers
  // 4. Effects
  
  return (
    // JSX
  )
}
```

### Tailwind CSS
- Use Tailwind utility classes (no custom CSS unless absolutely necessary)
- Group classes logically: layout → spacing → typography → colors → effects
- Use `clsx` or `cn` utility for conditional classes
- Define custom values in `tailwind.config.ts` (colors, spacing, etc.)
- Use responsive prefixes: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`
- Prefer Tailwind over inline styles

### Code Organization
```
app/
├── (auth)/           # Route group for authenticated pages
│   ├── dashboard/
│   ├── balance/
│   └── debtstatus/
├── (public)/         # Route group for public pages
